Material Information Summary

High-Grade Silver-Indium Drill Results at Orient East (QLD)

  • Key Drill Intercepts (Ag Equivalent Grades):
  • ORR097: 32m @ 63.6 g/t Ag Eq. (surface to 32m)
  • ORR099: 18m @ 210.6 g/t Ag Eq. (62m depth), incl. 9m @ 369.7 g/t Ag Eq.
  • ORR100: 86m @ 75.5 g/t Ag Eq. (80m depth), incl. 20m @ 179.1 g/t Ag Eq.
  • ORR102: 29m @ 150.0 g/t Ag Eq., incl. 1m @ 1,212.5 g/t Ag Eq. (333 g/t Ag, 9.39% Pb/Zn)

  • ORR107: 50m @ 107.2 g/t Ag Eq. (shallow), incl. 1m @ 925.0 g/t Ag Eq.

  • Exploration Target:

  • 25–35Mt @ 77–95 g/t Ag Eq. (inclusive of high-grade core: 12–18Mt @ 110–130 g/t Ag Eq.).

  • High-grade sub-zones: 3.5–4.0Mt @ 280–340 g/t Ag Eq.

  • Upcoming Catalysts:

  • Orient West JORC Resource: Expected by end-July 2025.
  • Orient East JORC Resource: Targeted for September 2025.
  • Additional Drilling: VTEM survey targets to be tested from late July.

Operational Highlights

  • Mineralisation Open: Extends over 320m strike, open at depth/west; potential for open-pit and underground mining.
  • Assays Pending: Results for holes ORR108–ORR118 outstanding.

Valuation Impact

  • Results reinforce Orient as Australia’s highest-grade silver-indium deposit, with scalability for resource growth.

Material Information Summary

(Exploration Results Announcement)

Key Highlights:

  • Tin assays received from the first 9 holes of a 50–60-hole drilling program (8,000–10,000m) at the Montezuma Antimony & Silver Project (Tasmania).
  • High-grade intercepts include:
  • 9.2m @ 0.77% Sn, 806 g/t AgEq, 1.13 g/t Au, 2.27% SbEq (MZS13).
  • 1.5m @ 2.77% Sn, 3,254 g/t AgEq, 3.26 g/t Au, 1.69% SbEq (MZS12).
  • 1.0m @ 3.06% Sn, 3,254 g/t AgEq, 1.54 g/t Au, 9.16% SbEq (MZS11).
  • Polymetallic mineralization: All holes show high-grade Sb, Ag, Au, Cu, Pb, and Sn.
  • Ongoing drilling: Mineralization remains open along strike and at depth.
  • Metallurgy: ALS commissioned for flotation tests (including tin/gold recovery analysis).

Market Context:

  • Antimony prices at record highs (~US$34,747/t) due to tight supply and China’s export restrictions.
  • Critical mineral status: Classified by Australian and Tasmanian governments.

No capital-raising, trading halt, or financial data disclosed.

Summary of ASX Announcement (AusQuest Limited - Exploration Update - Cangallo Copper Project):

Material Information for Trading/Capital Markets Decisions:

  • Exploration Results:
  • Multiple wide copper-gold intercepts reported in first four of 13 planned RC drill holes (e.g., 324m @ 0.30% Cu, 0.07ppm Au).
  • Mineralization starts near surface, remains open at depth and laterally.

  • Porphyry center not yet intersected—potential for higher grades in future drilling.

  • Metallurgical Results:

  • Preliminary leach tests show 60–80% copper recovery in 7/10 samples; acid consumption low to moderate (<28 kg/t).

  • Next Steps:

  • Stage 2 drilling completion by end-July 2025; assays for remaining holes expected by end-August 2025.
  • Diamond drilling planned for late August 2025 to target depth/extensions.

  • Stage 3 RC drilling permits pending (targeting southern extension).

  • Scale Potential:

  • Evidence of multiple porphyry centers; new surface samples suggest mineralized zone extends 1.2km south of current drilling.

Non-Material Omissions:

  • JORC tables, director commentary, general project background.

Trading Implication: Positive assay results and leach recoveries may support investor sentiment, but further drilling is critical to confirm scale/grade.

Here’s the material information extracted from the Patriot Battery Metals ASX announcement, formatted concisely for trading and capital markets decisions:

Mineral Resource Announcement (Caesium & Lithium)
- World’s largest pollucite-hosted caesium deposit confirmed at Shaakichiuwaanaan Project (Rigel & Vega zones):
- Rigel Zone (Indicated): 163,000t @ 10.25% Cs₂O, 1.78% Li₂O, 646ppm Ta₂O₅.
- Vega Zone:
- Indicated: 530,000t @ 2.61% Cs₂O, 2.23% Li₂O.
- Inferred: 1,698,000t @ 2.40% Cs₂O, 1.81% Li₂O.
- Total contained Cs₂O: 30.5kt (Indicated) + 40.8kt (Inferred).

  • Consolidated MRE (CV5 + CV13 Pegmatites, including Cs zones):
  • Indicated: 108.0Mt @ 1.40% Li₂O, 0.11% Cs₂O, 166ppm Ta₂O₅.

  • Inferred: 33.4Mt @ 1.33% Li₂O, 0.21% Cs₂O, 155ppm Ta₂O₅.

  • Key Highlights:

  • Caesium is supply-constrained globally, with potential applications in next-gen solar technologies.
  • Metallurgical studies underway (X-ray ore sorting) to recover Cs alongside Li/Ta.

  • Feasibility Study (lithium-only, CV5 Pegmatite) on track for Q3 2025 completion.

  • Valuation Impact:

  • Enhances project economics with high-value Cs by-product potential.
  • Confirms Shaakichiuwaanaan as a globally significant critical minerals asset.

Next Steps:
- Expand Cs resource drilling (Inferred → Indicated).
- Evaluate Cs integration into project development post-lithium feasibility study.

No capital raising, trading halt, or liquidity events announced. Focus remains on resource delineation and feasibility.
